SIMPLE: windiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Windiness
<hw>Wind"i*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being windy or tempestuous; <as>as, the
<ex>windiness</ex> of the weather or the season</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fullness of wind; flatulence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Tendency to generate wind or gas; tendency to
produce flatulence; <as>as, the <ex>windiness</ex> of
vegetables</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Tumor; puffiness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The swelling <qex>windiness</qex> of much knowledge.</q>
<rj><qau>Brerewood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Winding</ent>⟦br⟧
